      • authenticate

        String authenticate​(boolean verbose,
                    String consoleURL,
                    String username,
                    char[] password,
                    boolean consentConfirmed)
             throws CommandFailedException
        Authenticates user by name and password.
        Parameters:
        verbose - whether or not to print verbose debug messages/statuses.
        consoleURL - console URI to target.
        username - the username.
        password - the password.
        consentConfirmed - user confirmed to overwrite existing database.
        Returns:
        a bearer token to pass into copy(boolean, String, String, Source, boolean, String) later on.
        Throws:
        CommandFailedException - on authentication failure or some other unexpected failure.

          PushToCloudCommand.Source source,

   throws CommandFailedException
        Copies the given dump to the console URI.
        Parameters:
        verbose - whether or not to print verbose debug messages/statuses.
        consoleURL - console URI to target.
        boltUri - bolt URI to target database.
        source - dump to copy to the target.
        deleteSourceAfterImport - delete the dump after successful import
        bearerToken - token from successful authenticate(boolean, String, String, char[], boolean) call.
        Throws:
        CommandFailedException - on copy failure or some other unexpected failure.
